[b]Linux Install[/b]
Get the latest stable Linux release from the [b]files[/b] section. Unpack the [b].tar.gz[/b] file and follow these [b]commands[/b].
[code]
mv XCursor-Pro-Light ~/.icons                     # install as local
sudo mv XCursor-Pro-Light /usr/share/icons        # install as root
[/code]

[b]Linux Uninstall[/b]
[code]
rm -r ~/.icons/XCursor-Pro-Light                  # remove from local
sudo rm -r /usr/share/icons/XCursor-Pro-Light     # remove from root
[/code]

[b]Window Install[/b]
[1] unzip [b]XCursor-Pro-Light-Windows.zip[/b] file.
[2] Open [b]XCursor-Pro-Light-Windows/[/b] in Explorer, and [b]right-click[/b] on [b]install.inf[/b].
[3] Click 'Install' from the context menu, and authorize the modifications to your system.
[4] Open [i]Control Panel > Personalisation and Appearance > Change mouse pointers[/i], and select [b]XCursor-Pro-Light Cursors[/b].
[5] Click '[b]Apply[/b]'.

